      <p>When the documented steps don&rsquo;t hold, the cause is usually past the surface &mdash; genuine company-file (.QBW) integrity damage, a file corrupted or quarantined by malware with no clean backup to fall back on, or a file that was never completely created in the first place. A Certified ProAdvisor with active Desktop and Enterprise certifications diagnoses the actual root cause, repairs or recovers the file against a written scope, and verifies it opens cleanly before closing. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
